.TH "BSON_STRERROR_R" "3" "2014-05-29" "libbson"
.SH NAME
bson_strerror_r()
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
char *
bson_strerror_r (int    err_code,
                 char  *buf,
                 size_t buflen);
.fi
.fi

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B .B err_code
An errno.
.LP
.TP
.B .B buf
A location to store the string.
.LP
.TP
.B .B buflen
The size of
.B buf
\&.
.LP

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

This is a portability wrapper around
.B strerror()
\&.

.SH "RETURNS"

The passed in
.B buf
parameter or an internal string.


